stylometry: Me and Jimmy did our group project on sales of a popular video game Madden '12.  After getting information such as developer costs, production costs, advertising costs, licesing costs, and past sales numbers we used @risk simulation to give us the optimal amount for us to began to produce and sell to maximize profits. we used the inputs of minimum, maximum and most likely giving us a triangular distribution. following running @Risk we concluded going with our first simulaution that gave us a profit a little less than that of the other but had completely no standard deviation guarenteeing we would make that amount while the other showed a higher standard deviation.
